All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    BadEncodingException
    Exception thrown when an encoded string is not correct according to the appropriate fromString() method.
    BulkCargo
    Bulk cargo is commodity cargo that is transported unpacked in large quantities.
    BulkCargoType
    Represents the possible types that Bulk Cargo can be.
    BulkCarrier
    Represents a ship capable of carrying bulk cargo.
    BulkQuay
    A Bulk Quay is a type of quay specifically designed for the unloading of Bulk Carrier vessels.
    Cargo
    Denotes a cargo whose function is to be transported via a Ship or land transport.
    CargoDecompositionEvaluator
    Collects data on what types of cargo are passing through the port.
    CargoMovement
    The movement of cargo coming into or out of the port.
    Container
    Represents a shipping container, used for holding or transporting something.
    ContainerQuay
    A Container Quay is a type of quay specifically designed for the unloading of Container Ship vessels.
    ContainerShip
    Represents a ship capable of carrying shipping containers.
    ContainerType
    Represents the possible types of Containers a ship can carry.
    Encodable
    A type that can be encoded to a machine-readable string representation, useful for saving objects to files.
    Launcher
    Entry point for the GUI of the Port Simulation.
    Movement
    The movement of ships or cargo coming into or out of the port from land or sea.
    MovementDirection
    Represents the possible directions a ship or cargo can be moving.
    NauticalFlag
    Stores information about particular nautical flags flown by ships.
    NoSuchCargoException
    Exception thrown when a piece of cargo is requested by a given ID but no cargo with that ID exists.
    NoSuchShipException
    Exception thrown when a ship is requested by a given IMO number but no ship with that IMO number exists.
    Port
    A place where ships can come and dock with Quays to load / unload their cargo.
    PortCanvas
    Subclass of the JavaFX Canvas to represent the main elements of the port graphically.
    Quay
    Quay is a platform lying alongside or projecting into the water where ships are moored for loading or unloading.
    QuayOccupancyEvaluator
    Evaluator to monitor how many quays are currently occupied at the port.
    Ship
    Represents a ship whose movement is managed by the system.
    ShipFlagEvaluator
    Gathers data on how many ships each country has sent to this port.
    ShipMovement
    The movement of a ship coming into or out of the port.
    ShipQueue
    Queue of ships waiting to enter a Quay at the port.
    ShipThroughputEvaluator
    Gathers data on how many ships pass through the port over time.
    StatisticsEvaluator
    A base class representing an object that gathers and reports data on various aspects of the port's operation.
    Tickable
    Denotes a class whose state changes on every tick of the simulation.
    View
    View for the Port Simulation GUI.
    ViewModel
    View model for the Port Simulation GUI.
